column5: Good luck Andre. The Lake was very good to my group in late June. My last trip this year is at the end of September, much closer to the border.
I just check the forcast for next week: colder and some rain so cloudy day should help By mid-september it's going to be the start of the walleye best time of the year just close to home.
Just back and Lake Hebert has meet my expectations! Full report later.
